Initializing a repository:
- navigate to the folder in terminal and enter $ git init 

Check status:
- enter $ git status

Add files to the repository:
- $ git add .

Make a commit:
- git commit -am "message"
- the "a" tells Git to add all modified files to the current commit

Push to Github.com:
- $ git push origin master

Connecting to a folder on GitHub:
- run the command $ git remote add origin [copied web address]
- then perform the push $ git push origin master

